732955f-b.title: Social conditions in Manhattan.
732955f-b.text:
Social Conditions in Manhattan A series of 8 photos showing both internal and external aspects of a condemned tenement at No. 375 East 19th Street, (between Avenue's B.vC. Those showing the outside of this structure are duplicates of views classified under the location. This building, by personal investigation of the writer, is absent in April 1939, having been demolished as a part of the donors campaign for better living
quarters for the less privileged.
Fa11, 1938
Views: 1-8
Gift of Committee on Housing
Charity Organization Society

(On the map, it Looks like location is 10th Street, not 19th street, as it is written)
